# Movie Finder Frontend — Cursor Rules

This file is a legacy fallback. Cursor loads the richer MDC rules from `.cursor/rules/` automatically.

If your IDE supports MDC rules, the following files apply:
- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always active (frontend context, npm workflow)
- `.cursor/rules/angular.mdc` — activates on `**/*.ts`, `**/*.html`, `**/*.scss`
- `.cursor/rules/architect.mdc` — activates when designing component structure or SSE contracts
- `.cursor/rules/developer.mdc` — activates when implementing issues
- `.cursor/rules/debugger.mdc` — activates when investigating UI or SSE bugs

---

## Quick reference

**Repo:** `aharbii/movie-finder-frontend` · Primary context: `CLAUDE.md`

**Non-negotiables:**
- Standalone components only — no NgModules, ever
- Signals for all reactive state — no `BehaviorSubject` for component-local state
- Smart / Dumb component split — dumb components take `@Input()` only, never inject services
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type narrowing
- `npm run lint` and `npm run format` must pass before commit
- Never `--no-verify` on pre-commit
- Conventional Commits: `feat(ui): summary`
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR
